    "body": "### Problem\n\nSee `:h 'ignorecase'` and `:h 'smartcase'`\r\n\r\nThere is no mention of those options affecting insert mode completion or command line completion. But they do.\r\n\r\nIn general, this seems to be a problem with other options as well. The help docs do not comprehensively list everything an option affects. This can give users dread/anxiety when changing an option because they don't know all the behavior it modifies.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\r\n:h 'smartcase'\r\n:h 'ignorecase'\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nList everything the option affects. Perhaps in a bulleted or numbered list.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim -u DEFAULTS\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 12.6\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.25.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew",
